2014-02-27 00:18:53	smrtz|nix	Like, is there a keybind to swap it?
2014-02-27 00:18:58	technomancy	yeah
2014-02-27 00:19:16	smrtz|nix	ahh, I think I'd rather have a dip, unless it really is a lot more work?
2014-02-27 00:19:17	technomancy	you can set a key to jump to a specific layer, or momentarily switch to it, or to go up a layer or down a layer or whatever
2014-02-27 00:19:36	technomancy	depends
2014-02-27 00:19:48	technomancy	a dip might not be more work if you are already going to build your own PCB
2014-02-27 00:19:52	smrtz|nix	technomancy: Oh, so I could just have a random button, and you press it to swap the keys?
2014-02-27 00:20:00	technomancy	sure; it's fully configurable
2014-02-27 00:20:02	dfj	is all about how you do teh configuration in the code- either a key, or a combination of keys (if youare aiming for a 60-ish layout) can get you into a 'remap' mode, but - using one of the firmware out there that nearly does what you want as a starting point will likely save a lot of effort.
2014-02-27 00:20:08	technomancy	it's like ... turing-complete and shit
2014-02-27 00:20:26	technomancy	you can have a key that calculates the first ten fibbonaci numbers and enters them
